createPurl

public void createPurl(java.lang.String path,
                       java.lang.String type,
                       java.lang.String maintainers,
                       java.lang.String target,
                       java.lang.String seealso,
                       boolean useBasepurl,
                       boolean expectSuccess)
Create a new PURL via an HTTP POST.

Parameters:
path - A PURL path or id (starting with a '/' and containing its domains and name, e.g. /testdomain/subdomain/purlName).
type - The type of PURL (one of "301", "302", "303", "307", "404", "410", "clone", "chain", "partial").
maintainers - A comma-separated list of user or group names that are allowed to maintain the named PURL.
target - A URL to redirect to; used for PURLs of type 301, 302, 307 and partial.
seealso - A URL for See Also requests; used for PURLs of type 303.
useBasepurl - Whether or not to include a default basePURL for testing of PURLs of types clone or chain.
expectSuccess - Whether the test should expect to succeed. If false, it will expect to fail.

resolvePurl

public void resolvePurl(java.lang.String path,
                        java.lang.String control)
Resolve a PURL via HTTP GET.

Parameters:
path - A PURL path or id (starting with a '/' and containing its domains and name, e.g. /testdomain/subdomain/purlName).
control - An expected response string from the resolution. Generally, this will be a URL from a PURL's Location header.

Delete a PURL via HTTP DELETE.

Parameters:
path - A PURL path or id (starting with a '/' and containing its domains and name, e.g. /testdomain/subdomain/purlName).
expectSuccess - Whether the test should expect to succeed. If false, it will expect to fail.

registerUser

public void registerUser(java.lang.String uid,
                         java.lang.String name,
                         java.lang.String affiliation,
                         java.lang.String email,
                         java.lang.String passwd,
                         java.lang.String hint,
                         java.lang.String justification)
Register a new user via an HTTP POST. NB: Assumes that immediate user registration is available in the PURL server. To turn on immediate user registration, unset in src/mod-purl-admin/modules/mod-purl-admin/etc/PURLConfig.xml

Parameters:
uid - A user id (e.g. "dwood").
name - The name of the user (e.g. "David Wood").
affiliation - The user's affiliation (such as a company name).
email - The user's email address
passwd - The user's new password (to create the account; a password is not required to authenticate yet).
hint - A hint that they user can later user to remember their password.
justification - A justification as to why the account should be created (some PURL servers require this).

deleteUser

public void deleteUser(java.lang.String uid)
Delete a user via an HTTP DELETE.

Parameters:
uid - A user id (e.g. "dwood").

Parameters:
filename - The name of a file in the "testdata" directory that holds input data.
numCreated - The number of PURLs to be created in this operation.
